message.content:
cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SOC, cs.IR, cs.HC

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on using Twitter data to detect events in real-time.
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper discusses the development of a working system, SportSense.
- cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks) is another possible category as the paper explores the use of human sensors (Twitter users) to detect events.
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possible category as the paper discusses a novel event detection method based on measurement studies of tweets.
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also a possible category as the paper discusses the use of SportSense to empower novel services using a smart electronic TV program guide.
